GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 889
Short Title: Lumber River State Park Directives. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative B. Jones.
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: State and Local Government, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the
House
April 14, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO DIRECT THE DEPARTMENT OF NATURAL AND CULTURAL RESOURCES
3 TO ENTER INTO AN MOA FOR MANAGEMENT AND OPERATION OF CERTAIN
4 RECREATIONAL FACILITIES AND TO MOVE THE PARK HEADQUARTERS TO
5 THE TOWN OF FAIR BLUFF.
6 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
7 SECTION 1. The Department of Natural and Cultural Resources (Department) shall,
8 no later than March 1, 2026, negotiate a Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) for the Department
9 to (i) assume the management and operation of the River Walk, adjacent Park, and any associated
10 parking areas (collectively, the Facilities) in the Town of Fair Bluff (Town) as a unit of Lumber
11 River State Park (Park) and (ii) utilize the Town's Lumber River Visitors Center (Center) as the
12 Headquarters of the Park. The MOA shall include, at a minimum, the following:
13 (1) Delineation of the areas subject to the respective management of the Town
14 and the Department. The MOA may provide for shared management of
15 parking and other areas utilized for the River Walk, the Park, and the Center
16 and for other uses.
17 (2) The establishment, collection, and sharing of any user fees for property usage
18 and events operated at the Facilities and the Center. Nothing in this
19 subdivision is intended to (i) require the charging of admission to any property
20 or event or (ii) authorize the Department to charge an admission fee for use of
21 the Facilities or the Center other than during a festival or other special event
22 or as a rental fee for a private event.
23 (3) The adoption and enforcement of bylaws, rules, and guidelines needed for the
24 Department to carry out the management duties imposed by the MOA.
25 (4) The transfer or agreement on shared use, management, or implementation of
26 any assets, liabilities, contracts, or agreements between the Town and the
27 Department necessary to carry out the duties imposed on the Department and
28 Town by the MOA. Any delegation or transfer shall be made in accordance
29 with applicable law.
30 SECTION 2. The Department of Natural and Cultural Resources shall enter into the
31 Memorandum of Agreement required by Section 1 of this act no later than March 1, 2026, and
32 shall submit a copy of the Memorandum of Agreement to the Joint Legislative Oversight
33 Committee on Governmental Operations and the Fiscal Research Division prior to the convening
34 of the 2026 Regular Session of the 2025 General Assembly.
*H889-v-1*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 SECTION 3. This act is effective when it becomes law.
